<br>
Note: I do not deal drugs, I don't do hard drugs, I buy what I need for friends and I in quantity so all can be happy.<br>
<br>
After my regular PM shift at my work place, a female friend and I decided to go out that night.  This particular female is a heavy drinker, but only ended up having 4 canned beers at the bar we went to.  I on the other hand smoked profusely for the few hours we were driving after the bar.  <br>
<br>
Keep in mind I did not drink.  In fact, I really don't care for drinking as marijuana is a fast, effective relaxent to me.  Anyways to the point of the story, said female had 4 beers, which normally she can do with ease, but on this particular night she was without a doubt unable to drive.  But on the other hand after &quot;I&quot; drove HER home, I went out for another 2 hours smoking almost constantly.  I believe the effects of marijuana do inhibit your reactions etc, but its is VERY easy to control if you are either used to it, or just take it easy.  <br>
<br>
To me, alcohol is the worst of America's problems.  Depression, anger, wife beating, the list goes on.  Granted marijuana induces the supposed &quot;Drug-Dealers&quot;, supposedly supports Afghans, and as a whole seems to be the hell send to the nation.  <br>
<br>
Why is marijuana so bad?  It grows naturally, and when cultured can be harnessed for great phsychological and emotional effects, dulls pain, reduces chances at Glaucoma, easily - EASILY attainable, and its cheap, fast and effective.<br>
<br>
This is the choice for kids now adays.  Who the hell cares if its illegal, as today's youth has readily accepted marijuana on an every day basis.  I could go to school and buy a quarter pound at any time I wanted.  Drive around, boom you know who to ask, all it takes is a phone call and its delivered.<br>
<br>
Alcohol on the other hand requires 19 year olds etc that want to have any affects would have to find a carry-out, know a good bar keep, or end up stealing it.  <br>
<br>
Again these are just MY opinions, and I did write an essay for my college course - &quot;Marijuana: To Legalize or Not&quot;<br>
<br>
On to the point about the supposed Gateway drug.  To me (again my opinion) the drug itself is not a gateway.  Its the people that you must contend with to get the drug.  Say if you were in a nice Suburban nieghborhood and your next door nieghbor grew his own herbs, you would simply walk over, admire his lawn and buy a bag from him.  He's not cooking meth, he's not boiling crack, just a good ol' boy growing dope. <br>
<br>
Now let's say you were downtown Milwaukee (or any city/place for the matter) and you started hanging with a group of people that you know can get pot easily.  Pretty soon these people may start smoking crack, and eventually you will be tempted to smoke it as well.  Next comes the Extacy (heroin as well), and many more X-drugs.  <br>
<br>
See my point?  Well I thank you all for reading through this and please try to remember its just an opinion based on MY own experiences I thought I could do good sharing.<br>
<br>
As a side note, I work at a Nursing home where I get compliments every day on my good natured, compassionate work.  I make people laugh and just have a blast with my co-workers.  I have gotten 3 raises in the last 6 months due to this work and continue to get high honors among the clinic.  I do not smoke before work, I don't smoke during work.  I smoke on the way home AFTER work, before I go to bed, or before I go out and party.  I tend not to smoke if I know I must be doing something (ie. family gathering or the such)<br>
<br>
